{
  "stem": "1736.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, sure.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there were many incidents.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I think we can-- without going into lots of details on the incidents-- the major event as far as the Jewish life and the synagogues, cultural things were concerned, not only in Dessau but in Germany generally, of course took place towards the end of 1938, in fact on the 9th of November '38, when a decree was made by the Nazi party to destroy all Jewish synagogues, burn the-- set fire to all the books, destroy Jewish shops, and whatever they could lay their hands on.",
      "word_count": 88
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It so happened, like I mentioned before, that I was in Dessau attending [HEBREW], and it also so happened that the [HEBREW], which I think I mentioned before was in the little room where Moses Mendelssohn was born, was opposite on the same street, opposite the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We heard a lot of commotion.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We heard a lot of noise.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Ran out, and there I saw people marching up to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, groups of people in uniform, both brown and black, meaning the SR and SS, and with mobs of others shouting, [GERMAN], which means 'death to the Jews.' And-- now, even though I was very well known in-- in Aken, in Dessau, I was like a young fellow, a young kid.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I also had made it a habit to wear a clothing very similar to the Hitler Youth, which sort of protected me in a way.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There wore black.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I wore navy blue, but it was--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there were shorts and socks.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, it was just-- you know, I had no insignias or anything like this, but the colors matched in, so I-- that I didn't stand out from the--",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As a Jew.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
